'''Todd Day''' (born [[January 7]], [[1970]] in [[Decatur, Illinois]]) is a professional [[basketball]] player who was selected in the 1st round (8th pick) by the [[Milwaukee Bucks]] in the [[1992 NBA Draft]]. He was traded with [[Alton Lister]] to the [[Boston Celtics]] for [[Sherman Douglas]] on 11/26/1995. Day scored a career high 41 points against the [[Minnesota Timberwolves]] on 12/22/1995. Other teams that Day has played for during his NBA career were the [[Miami Heat]], [[Phoenix Suns]], and [[Minnesota Timberwolves]]. Day played his college ball at the [[University of Arkansas]] and had a career scoring average of 20.7 ppg.



